# Zod Schema Validation Standards (TypeScript Scope)

Apply these standards whenever working in TypeScript code that handles external input (API routes, Server Actions, forms, query params, and client-submitted payloads).

## Requirements

- Define Zod schemas before executing business logic.
- Infer types using `z.infer<typeof SchemaName>`.
- Do not create duplicate manually maintained interfaces for validated payloads.
- Validate at boundaries and fail fast on invalid input.

## Backend/API Pattern

```ts
const parseResult = inputSchema.safeParse(await request.json());
if (!parseResult.success) {
  return NextResponse.json(
    { errors: parseResult.error.format() },
    { status: 400 }
  );
}
const input: Input = parseResult.data;
```

## Frontend/Form Pattern

```ts
const form = useForm<FormInput>({
  resolver: zodResolver(formSchema),
});
```
